Another place where Muir didn't know everything!  I can't help you in your
present situation, but next time leave the shroud alone and remove the fan
from the front (FIF) side of the shroud and remove the generator without
lifting the shroud.

> The old generator's axis is worn out. Can I replace it myself? Does it need
> major overhaul in a shop?

If the shaft is bad, a rebuilt generator is probably indicated.  Might be
a good time to consider swapping to a late model alternator.

